FBIS4-7282 "dreas083__a94007" FBIS-EAS-94-083-A Daily Report 29 April 1994 ANNEX Japan SDPJ To Join Sakigake, Others in Floor Group SDPJ To Join Sakigake, Others in Floor Group OW2904043094 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 29 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW2904043094 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database Japanese BFN [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 29 April Morning Edition] [Text] In a NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN interview on 28 April, Chairman Tomiichi Murayama of the Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] showed a positive attitude toward formation of a joint floor group with Sakigake [Harbinger] and some other groups. He noted the SDPJ will formally seek formation of the SDPJ-Sakigake floor group at the lower house after Golden Week recess in May, opening party head and executive talks on a regular basis. He said: "We would like to open formal talks with Sakigake after the recess in May." In the interview, Murayama stressed the need for the joint floor group with the Sakigake, saying: "We should build closer relations with Sakigake." On top of that, he hinted at his positive attitude toward a tie-up with certain quarters in the Japan New Party and the Democratic Socialist Party, noting: "In addition to Sakigake, we would like to seek cooperation with other people we can get along with."
